The paper discusses a method for training deep neural networks on distributed data, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The specific application of the method is for brain segmentation using structural magnetic resonance imaging (sMRI) datasets, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves consolidating the weights of separate neural networks, which is a technique used in deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the method using a case study, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for analyzing the results.
